Buckeye Plans Oil-Product Pipeline Upgrades in March, April

-- B y   P a u l   B u r k h a r d t
-- 
2011-03-09T21:22:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/buckeye-plans-oil-product-pipeline-upgrades-in-march-april.html
  Buckeye Partners LP (BPL)  plans to
temporarily interrupt deliveries to some terminals in  New
Jersey ,  Pennsylvania  and New York during this month and April to
update equipment at the locations, according to a bulletin to
shippers.  Gasoline and distillate service to the companyâ€™s  Long
Island City  and Inwood terminals in New York will be shut late
on March 16 for less than 24 hours, the notice indicated.  Stations in Linden, New Jersey; Macungie, Pennsylvania; and
Auburn, New York, will shut April 7 from 5:30 a.m. to 9:30 p.m.
local time, with no pipeline movements in or out available. The
stations will also shut during the same hours on April 14,
Buckeye said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
